		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_65484082"><p><div class="quote"><p>every source of information I've ever come across in my life has some non-zero probability of inaccuracy</p></div><p>What that chance &gt;60%?  Because that's what you're getting with silly chatbots.</p><p>Further, the nature and type of mistakes you'll find in other sources are fundamentally different from the kind chatbots produce.   As for people's trust in their output, they look to the average person like an all-knowing guru.  They blindly trust the output because the output looks credible, especially when it includes a "source" and because of all the media hype telling them how amazing they are.</p><p><div class="quote"><p> intelligent reading requires questioning everything that I read</p></div><p>Nonsense.  That would be par<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
