	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_65483820"><p>The point is, for me anyway, that I don't have to do the typing!</p><p>I *am* a good programmer, but there's a lot of boilerplate that sucks when you have to type it all out (or copy/paste from an old project or example then customize to fit the current project). I can tell it HOW to make a program work and get it to do all the boring parts. Sure, it's just going out there and copy/pasting whatever, but it's also doing a search and replace for me.</p><p>The only time I've had trouble with AI programming is when I ask it to do something clever. It doesn't do clever very well. But if I give it my "clever" code and ask it to do something boring and mundane with it? It does a great job with that.</p></div>
	</div>

