<div id="comment_65483764" class="cw">
	<div id="comment_top_65483764" class="commentTop newcomment">
		<div class="title">
			<h4><a rel="nofollow" id="comment_link_65483764" name="comment_link_65483764" href="//slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=23730478&amp;cid=65483764" onclick="return D2.setFocusComment(65483764)" >ChatGPT has been a lifesaver for me</a>


		 	<span id="comment_score_65483764" class="score"> (<a href="#" onclick="getModalPrefs('modcommentlog', 'Moderation Comment Log', 65483764); return false"><span class=opt>Score:</span>4</a>, Interesting)</span></h4>
		</div>
		<div class="details">
			<span class="by"><span class="byby">by </span><a rel="nofollow" href="//slashdot.org/~dhjdhj">dhjdhj</a>  <span class="uid"><a rel="nofollow" href="//slashdot.org/~dhjdhj">( 1355079 )</a></span></a></span><span class="writes" style="display:none"> writes:</span> 
			<span class="otherdetails" id="comment_otherdetails_65483764">		
		on Sunday June 29, 2025 @08:07AM (<span class="ind"></span><a rel="nofollow" href="//slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=23730478&amp;cid=65483764">#65483764</a>)
		<small> </small>
</span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_65483764">This tool has both saved me time and also rescued me from some emergencies.
Examples:
I used it to write GUI functions. It&rsquo;s not that I don&rsquo;t know how to do such things but it can do in 1 minute what would take me a1/2 hour so it&rsquo;s a massive time saver. I just have to check the code and sometimes tweak it a bit. I consider this to be &ldquo;busywork&rdquo; but that alone saves thousands of dollars a month in developer costs.

Last year I deleted an entry in a SQL database table  not realizing that cascading delete was enabled and I ended up deleting license keys for about 2,000 customers. There was no backup because the person who implemented the backup had recently died and his backup implementation had started failing due to changes in SSH keys.However, the information was available in a database managed by our payment fulfillment company via a pretty complicated REST API. I was able to instruct ChatGPT to &ldquo; write a python function to retrieve customer information from that company and generate a SQLinsert query to merge it back into our own database&rdquo;.  After a little tweaking, the damn thing gave me a function that just worked. Since I rarely use Python and SAL, It would have taken me hours if not days to both decipher that REST API, figure out the right SQL query and write the python code. Major customer catastrophe averted.

Separately from the above, I&rsquo;ve found it very useful for quick how-to tips when using applications that I don&rsquo;t use much, e.g. how do I do&rdquo;X&rdquo; in Photoshop, etc.

If I was a young recent graduate, I would be very concerned about my future opportunities and I remain very concerned how such tools will have detrimental affect on society due to how well AI can replace what previously required significant expertise and experience,</div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_65483764">
