	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_65483892"><p>I rountinely use LLMs for cleaning up prose in various reports.  As a proofreader and editor, it's the best tool I've ever found.</p><p>For creating reports from scratch, you have to be careful.  It's not perfect, but it will get you 85% to 95% of the way there on a first cut once you feed it the data. It's no replacement for a human, but it does save a lot of time.</p><p>I also use it for email.  When I have an important email to send out that must be "perfect", I'll run my draft through ChatGPT and ask it for a review, and to show me what it changed, and why.  More than once, it has caught a missing word or a clumsy phrase.</p><p>So yes, LLMs are not a gimmick, and they do increase productivity if used correctly.</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_65483892">
