			<span class="by"><span class="byby">by </span><a rel="nofollow" href="//slashdot.org/~Mr.+Dollar+Ton">Mr. Dollar Ton</a>  <span class="uid"><a rel="nofollow" href="//slashdot.org/~Mr.+Dollar+Ton">( 5495648 )</a></span></a></span><span class="writes" style="display:none"> writes:</span> 
			<span class="otherdetails" id="comment_otherdetails_65484030"></span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_65484030"><p>It is completely worthless for anything that isn't completely trivial.</p><p>Even the glorified pay-for-use versions.</p><p>Software, electronic hardware, history questions - no matter what you ask it, the "AI" is worthless.</p><p>There is limited utility in some machine learning methods when sifting through bad data from physics experiments, but even there the applications need triple checking.</p><p>The only thing where the "AI" excels is creating trolling posts for maga-like readers.</p></div>
	</div>

